This paper discusses the implementation of digital predistortion (DPD) on modern embedded processors, which involves signal processing and optimization techniques. Therefore, it is likely to belong to the Information Theory (cs.IT), Architecture (cs.AR), Embedded Systems (cs.EM), Systems and Control (cs.SY), and Machine Learning (cs.LG) sub-categories.
